commit ac3e50f4b1c7505aebdff5e93e2b4b809c3e6a55
Author: Alexandros Bantis <ambantis@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Sep 8 15:36:44 2012 -0700

    Changed com.x460dot11.data.Database.updateBug method by syncronized.
    
    Now, users can request edit pages as much as they want, but once they enter the method, it is locked so that no other thread can make any updates (editBug.jsp). Once it enters the method, there is a second check to query the existing bug record that the user started with versus what currently exists in the database. Thus, there is a double check to guard against lost updates.

commit b237b5cf8b76afcad63f256e9477934266bfb9b4
Author: Alexandros Bantis <ambantis@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Sep 8 13:34:21 2012 -0700

    Changed edit bug process to prevent lost updates.
    
    Before a Database processes an editBug request, it queries bugdb for the updated value of the bug being edited. If the values are not the same (between the original version the user edited and what is currently in the database, then the update operation is aborted and throws an exception.

